            <p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="1"><blockquote><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1">quote:</font><hr><i>Originally posted by Sassinak </i><br />
<b> except aegolism </b><hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
Aegolism;<br />
Increase HP total 1100<br />
Increase Current HP 1100<br />
Increase AC by 54<br />
<br />
Thats at/above/right below almost 40% of an unbuffed, non-uber 55 plus warrior's total hitpoints.<br />
<br />
Add in the less damage from the added 54ac.<br />
<br />
Jug can solo in Skyfire... unbuffed... if I want to play the "jesus I hope I get some high crippling blows on this bastard..." on a low dark blue con.  I don't have the luxury of fear kiting, dotting (unless I get a proc) or healing myself.  (once again, unless I get some proc's)<br />
<br />
Add in the fact that until the patch last night, it wasn't even worth it due to decrease in XP on mobs over ten levels lower than you.<br />
<br />
I would love to see you tank a level 50 mob Sass, by yourself, unbuffed, and see how long you last without healer back up.  I know guys like Jave, Dika, Mattez, Gosplat, Ailerini and other uber warriors on server that might get the mob to half health before having to make the call on wether or not to beat feet to the zoneline or roll the dice and hope they're lucky when they go berserk.  Mind you, thats UNBUFFED.  With all the gear these guys probably have on or laying around in the bank, I'm sure it might be a possiblity soloing something like that.  They can self buff... a luxury 90% of the warriors on server do not have. (yay jboots... lol) Add in the weapons they have laying around... well... who's gonna have access to those weapons?  Certainly not 99% of the warriors on server.<br />
<br />
Thats what these changes are about, making it so "nearly everyone" that can and will solo will get the bonus of the added xp for the harder mobs.  <br />
<br />
Top that off with the added xp bonus for grouping.  <br />
<br />
Tack on the fact that an SK or a Pally can do everything a warrior can do in an XP group <b>and </b> then some.<br />
<br />
Nearly everyone doesn't include warriors.<br />
<br />
-J</font></p>
             
