            <p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="1">Well, throw a few peridots at a cleric, and you have aego for a couple hours.  No different from casters saying "soloing" when in fact they do not even try to do it without KEI.<br />
<br />
As for level 50 mobs... there's a vast difference between them and level 45 mobs, and I wouldn't expect any unbuffed melee to solo level 50 mobs (except perhaps through tricks like feign/bandage or fear kiting).  But there are vast differences amongst level 50 mobs too.  I would never expect to be able to solo a spite golem, but I'd like my chances against a swirlspine seahorse.  And I'd expect a run-of-the-mill warrior in fierce heraldic with purchased weapons like SBOZ to do pretty much as well as I do.</font></p>
             
